    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="landing-section faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
      <div class="container container--landing">
        <div class="section-intro">
          <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is Lulu a veterinary app?</summary>
            <p>No. Lulu is a personal health journal for pet owners. It helps you track and organize information — it does not diagnose conditions or replace professional veterinary care.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Can I use Lulu for more than one pet?</summary>
            <p>Yes. You can create separate profiles for each pet, each with its own check-ins, logs, and health history.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Can I export my pet's history?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Lulu lets you generate PDF reports from your pet's journal data, which you can review and share using your device's sharing options.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is my data private?</summary>
            <p>Your data is stored securely and tied to your account. We do not sell your personal information. See our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>When will Lulu be available?</summary>
            <p>Lulu is currently in App Store review. Join us soon — we're working hard to bring a calm, thoughtful pet health journal to iPhone.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
